            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f:\mathbb {R}^n\to \mathbb {R}]]></fr:tex> be twice continuously differentiable in an open neighborhood of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {x_\star }]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
            <html:p><html:strong>Necessary.</html:strong> If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {x_\star }]]></fr:tex> is a local minimizer, then
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(i)\ \nabla  f(\mathbf {x_\star })=\mathbf {0};\qquad  (ii)\ \nabla ^2 f(\mathbf {x_\star })\succeq \mathbf {0}.]]></fr:tex>
That is, it is a <fr:link href="/003P/" title="Stationary point" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/003P/" display-uri="003P" type="local">stationary point</fr:link> whose Hessian is <fr:link href="/003A/" title="Positive (semi)definiteness" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/003A/" display-uri="003A" type="local">positive semidefinite</fr:link>.</html:p>
            <html:p><html:strong>Sufficient.</html:strong> If instead <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\nabla  f(\mathbf {x_\star })=\mathbf {0}]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\nabla ^2 f(\mathbf {x_\star })\succ \mathbf {0}]]></fr:tex> (Hessian strictly positive definite), then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {x_\star }]]></fr:tex> is a strict local minimizer. The gap between <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\succeq ]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\succ ]]></fr:tex> is exactly the ambiguity the <fr:link href="/I6DT/" title="First-order optimality condition" uri="https://kellenkanarios.com/I6DT/" display-uri="I6DT" type="local">first-order condition</fr:link> alone cannot resolve.</html:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
